# pinned binaries check.sh downloads to keep local runs aligned with the CI
.ci-tools/

# The CI's Python tooling (semgrep, zizmor) — SUBTRACTED from the dependency scan.
# osv-scanner honours this .gitignore: listed here, the file is NOT scanned (`scan -r .`).
# It must nevertheless stay VERSIONED — the CI runs `pip install -r requirements-ci.txt` — so it is
# tracked via `git add -f` (same pattern as .envrc/CLAUDE.md). Renovate indexes TRACKED files, not
# the .gitignore: it keeps bumping the scanner (proven). NEVER `git rm --cached` this file.
# WHY subtract it: this is dev tooling, never shipped to a runtime. Resolving its transitive graph
# only surfaces CVEs of CI tools (their own `python-multipart`, `mcp`… deps) — noise, not the
# product's attack surface. The real application manifests are NOT ignored, so they ARE scanned.
/requirements-ci.txt

# misc
.DS_Store
*.log
*.bak
*.bak-*

# test tooling (Playwright MCP session artifacts)
.playwright-mcp/
